Author: claude-opus47-app <claude-opus47-app@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 23 15:00:32 2026 +0800

    fix(ldc): DEC-V61-050 Codex round 1 fixes — 1 HIGH + 4 MED + 1 LOW
    
    Codex GPT-5.4 post-merge review on DEC-V61-050 batches 1-4 returned
    CHANGES_REQUIRED with:
    - [HIGH] closure footer unconditionally claimed FULLY_SATISFIED even
      when D6/D7/D8 metrics could be null → lies to student on degraded run
    - [MED #2] psi ψ wall-closure residual (3.4e-3) is 2000× BIGGER than
      D8 BL ψ_gold (1.75e-6) and 270× larger than D8 BR ψ_gold (1.25e-5).
      The "2/2 PASS" we celebrated was argmax coincidence in a noise-
      dominated field, not validated physics
    - [MED #3] cache key used float st_mtime with 1e-6 tol + ignored bounds
      → stale-serve risk across APFS↔ext4 copies + explicit-bounds calls
    - [MED #4] fail-soft except too narrow — pyvista/VTK raise RuntimeError
      / TypeError / KeyError / pyvista.core.errors.* that would 500 the
      endpoint instead of nullably degrading D7/D8
    - [MED #5] frontend D2/D4 multiplied data.paper.tolerance_pct by 100
      even though backend already sent 5.0 → UI displayed ±500.0% for
      half a day
    - [LOW #6] DEC frontmatter batch 4 commit still "TBD" after push
    
    Round 1 fixes:
    
    1. [HIGH] LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx closure footer: gated on all of
       D6/D7/D8 having metrics + D8 signal_above_noise; shows 3 states
       — "3/4 validated · D8 below noise floor" (current reality),
       "4/4 all validated" (future when Poisson ψ lands), or "degraded"
       (when cache/pyvista missing on backend).
    
    2. [MED #2] psi_extraction.py: new psi_wall_closure_residuals() that
       returns max |ψ|/UL on each of the 4 walls. comparison_report.py
       calls it once after the ψ grid is computed and writes the result
       into metrics_primary_vortex/secondary_vortices entries as
       signal_to_residual_ratio + signal_above_noise (threshold = 3.0).
       Secondary D8 all_pass is now gated on signal_above_noise — so
       BL/BR honestly report all_pass=False (SNR 0.0005 and 0.0037
       respectively). D7 primary SNR 30.4× is still solid PASS.
       UI adds a rose-banner on D8 with the full reasoning. gold YAML
       updates:
         - secondary_vortices precondition: satisfied_by_current_adapter
           flipped to false with evidence_ref explaining the noise-floor
           issue + pointing to Poisson solve / native ψ as the fix path
         - contract_status: FULLY_SATISFIED_ALL_4_GHIA_TABLES →
           SATISFIED_FOR_U_V_AND_PRIMARY_VORTEX_NOT_SECONDARIES
       Honest retraction — 3/4 validated, not 4/4.
    
    3. [MED #3] Cache key now uses st_mtime_ns (integer, exact) + st_size
       (catches content change when mtime reused) + bounds tuple (explicit-
       bounds calls don't collide with cached-default) + schema_version
       (bumped to 2 — old caches deleted). No tolerance math on mtime.
    
    4. [MED #4] comparison_report.py wrapper: except (ImportError, OSError,
       ValueError) → except Exception, with a comment explaining why broad
       catch is warranted (optional viz dim; u_centerline D1-D5 is not
       guarded by this try/except). New PsiExtractionError class added to
       psi_extraction.py for callers that want to distinguish genuine
       extractor failure from "no data at all" — the public functions
       still return None on soft failures (contract unchanged).
    
    5. [MED #5] frontend: removed the erroneous * 100 on
       data.paper.tolerance_pct in two places (D2 + D4). Before fix the
       UI showed ±500.0% where it meant ±5.0%. D6/D7/D8 panels that I
       wrote already used .toFixed(1) without * 100 so were not affected.
    
    6. [LOW #6] DEC frontmatter commits_in_scope: TBD → 1f1ff6b +
       e5dd20e (sync log).
    
    Live API smoke post-fix (with schema-v2 cache regenerated):
      D6 v_centerline:      12/17 @ ±5.0% (UI now renders 5.0% not 500%)
      D7 primary vortex:    all_pass=True · SNR 30.45× · signal_above_noise=True
      D8 BL:                all_pass=False · SNR 0.0005× · below noise
      D8 BR:                all_pass=False · SNR 0.0037× · below noise
      psi_wall_residuals.max: 3.40e-3 (exposed in API for UI banner)
    
    The D8 retraction is the substance of this commit. The other 5 fixes
    are correctness/hygiene. A future DEC must either implement a Poisson
    ψ solve or sample ψ natively in OpenFOAM before D8 can honestly PASS.
    
    Tests: 27/27 pass under python3.11 (existing comparison_report tests
    unchanged; new dimensions don't have test coverage yet — documented
    as a follow-up).
    
