MEDIUM:
- [ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:1868): the degraded branch is fixed, but the advertised 3-state closure footer is not actually implemented. `missing.length > 0` correctly renders the degraded state, yet the non-degraded branch always renders `3 / 4 Ghia 观测量已验证` plus the D8 noise-floor explanation at [1891-1906](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:1891). `d8_noise_floor` only changes colors, and it is derived from `!data.metrics_secondary_vortices.all_pass`, not from a dedicated D8-above-noise aggregate. So a future real 4/4 D8 pass would still be reported as 3/4, and any future D8 fail for a reason other than noise floor would still be misexplained as noise-floor coincidence.
- [ui/backend/services/psi_extraction.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/ui/backend/services/psi_extraction.py:118): the cache-key fix is only partial. The read path expects `cached["bounds"].item()` at [124](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/ui/backend/services/psi_extraction.py:124), but the write path stores `bounds=np.array(bounds_key, dtype=object)` at [192](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/ui/backend/services/psi_extraction.py:192). For explicit 5-tuple bounds, that round-trips as a size-5 object array, so `.item()` raises `ValueError` and the loader silently falls back to recompute. I reproduced this under `python3.11`. Default `bounds=None` is fine, so current LDC runtime is safe, but the claim that the cache key now fully covers and works for explicit bounds is not yet true.

